title: High school football: Big win clinches conference title for Hinsdale South
text:
High school football: Big win clinches conference title for Hinsdale South   12:28 a.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
DARIEN â€“ Sean McCormack passed for 159 yards and four touchdowns in a 49-7 win against Morton. 
The Hornets finished the regular season with a 6-3 record and won the West Suburban Gold conference thanks to a Willowbrook loss against Leyden. 
Robert Hall and Ravon Johnson each had two touchdown receptions while Shawn Wimberly had a rushing touchdown. South led 49-0 before a late Morton touchdown. 
Hinsdale South will keep its season going in the Class 6A playoffs.
